approach to combatting the novel coronavirus – or COVID-19 – throughout 
the tri-state area.</p>
<p>These uniform standards will limit crowd capacity for social and 
recreational gatherings to 50 people effective 8 PM tonight. This 
follows updated guidance that the U.S. Centers for Disease Control and 
Prevention issued yesterday recommending the cancellation or 
postponement of in-person events consisting of 50 people or more.</p>
<p>The three governors also announced that restaurants and bars that 
serve food will temporarily be required to move to take-out and delivery
